Module com.example.epj2
Package com.example.epj2.model.rent

Class Rent

java.lang.Object
com.example.epj2.model.rent.Rent
public class Rent extends Object
Represents the rent of an electric vehicle. This class provides methods to access and manipulate rent attributes.

  • Constructor Details

    • Rent

      public Rent(LocalDateTime dateTime, String user, String vehicleId, int startX, int startY, int endX, int endY, int duration, boolean hasMalfunction, boolean hasPromotion)
      Constructs a new Rent object with specified attribute.
      Parameters:
      dateTime - the date and time the rent was made
      user - the username of the user who rented the electric vehicle
      vehicleId - the identifier of the rented electric vehicle
      startX - the starting position of the rent on the x-axis
      startY - the starting position of the rent on the y-axis
      endX - the ending position of the rent on the x-axis
      endY - the ending position of the rent on the y-axis
      duration - the duration of the rent in seconds
      hasMalfunction - true if a malfunction happened during the rent of the vehicle, false otherwise
      hasPromotion - true if there is rent promotion, false otherwise
